  "steps": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "text": "In a food processor, combine the basil, pine nuts, Parmesan, garlic, and salt and puree"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "While the motor is running, drizzle in the oil until incorporated"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Season with pepper to taste"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Use immediately or store in the refrigerator with a piece of plastic wrap placed right on the surface of the sauce to prevent discoloration (lasts up to 3 days, or 1 month in the freezer)"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "To make a cream sauce, heat up the heavy cream in a saucepan over medium-high heat until just hot"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "Remove from the heat and whisk in the pesto"
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "text": "Using a spatula, scrape the cream sauce into a bowl"
